Phn 1: Gii thiu:

in thoi - Vt dng khng th thiu trong cuc sng hin nay khi m ton cu ang tin ti cng ngh ha mi th trong cuc sng. Vi nhng chc nng a dng v ngy cng hin i (nh son vn bn Word, xem phim vi phn gii cao,), cng thm nhng chic in thoi ngy nay c kh nng c nhng thit b khc (nh my nh, my nhn tin, my ghi m,) th vic cng nhiu ngi chn in thoi l vt bt ly thn l khng th chi ci.

Nhn thy iu , nhm 2 nhn thc c rng vic ngi mua hng la chn cu hnh v gi c khi mua in thoi lun c ngi tiu dng t ln hng u. Do vy, hiu r hn v s nh hng ca nhng chc nng, cu hnh in thoi ti gi c, nhm 2 chn ti l: Phn tch m hnh d on gi in thoi qua cu hnh my.

V trong ti ny, dataset c nhm 2 thng nht s dng c tn l Mobile Phone Specifications and Prices c ti xung t Kaggle v tc gi ca dataset l PRATIK GARAI. Theo tc gi, dataset c ly t website Gadgets360 - l mt trang bo ca n c cp nht cc thng tin trn ton th gii, d liu t trang ny c scrapped v cleaned bng cch dng code y v preprocessed y

c d liu t file data.csv:

data<-read.csv("./data.csv")

Chuyn i Rupee (n v tin t ca n ) sang Dollar M

data['Price'] = data['Price']*0.012

Xem thuc tnh v mt vi dng d liu:

Phn 3: Kim nh gi thuyt:

Do dataset ca nhm c 3 loi bin l binary, continuous v nominal, nn phn kim nh gi thuyt nhm s p dng phng php kim k cho ph hp vi tng trng hp.

3 phng php kim k m nhm s s dng:

  • Phn tch tng quan Pearson cho 2 bin continuous.

  • One-way ANOVA F-test cho bin nominal v continuous.

  • Phn tch tng quan Point Biserial cho bin binary v continous.

Bin phn loi:

Brand

Phng php: One-way ANOVA F-test.

H0: Khng c s khc bit v gi trung bnh gia cc hng in thoi.

H1: C s khc bit v gi trung bnh gia cc hng in thoi.

new_data<-data
new_data<-new_data[order(new_data$Brand),]
new_brand = `as.factor`(new_data$Brand)
new_price = new_data$Price
new_brand<-as.numeric(new_brand)
summary(aov(new_price~new_brand))
##               Df   Sum Sq Mean Sq F value Pr(>F)
## new_brand      1    15956   15956    0.57   0.45
## Residuals   1359 38013023   27971

Do p = 0.369 > 0.05 => Khng c s khc bit v gi trung bnh gia cc hng in thoi.

Touchscreen

Phng php: Phn tch tng quan Point Biserial.

H0: Khng c s khc bit v gi trung bnh gia in thoi c cm ng v khng c cm ng.

H1: C s khc bit v gi trung bnh gia in thoi c cm ng v khng c cm ng.

new_data<-data
new_data[new_data$Touchscreen == "Yes",]['Touchscreen']<-as.integer(1)
new_data[new_data$Touchscreen == "No",]['Touchscreen']<-as.integer(0)
new_data$Touchscreen<-as.numeric(new_data$Touchscreen)
cor.test(new_data$Price,new_data$Touchscreen)
## 
##  Pearson's product-moment correlation
## 
## data:  new_data$Price and new_data$Touchscreen
## t = 1.8668, df = 1359, p-value = 0.06214
## alternative hypothesis: true correlation is not equal to 0
## 95 percent confidence interval:
##  -0.002567902  0.103433065
## sample estimates:
##        cor 
## 0.05057501

cor != 0=> C mi quan h tuyn tnh gia Touchscreen v gi.

Operating System

Phng php: One-way ANOVA F-test.

H0: Khng c s khc bit v gi trung bnh gia in thoi c h iu hnh khc nhau.

H1: C s khc bit v gi trung bnh gia in thoi c h iu hnh khc nhau.

new_data<-data
new_data<-new_data[order(new_data$OS),]
new_OS = as.numeric(as.factor(new_data$OS))
new_price = new_data$Price
summary(aov(new_OS~new_price))
##               Df Sum Sq Mean Sq F value   Pr(>F)    
## new_price      1   21.0  20.981   30.35 4.31e-08 ***
## Residuals   1359  939.5   0.691                     
## ---
## Signif. codes:  0 '***' 0.001 '**' 0.01 '*' 0.05 '.' 0.1 ' ' 1

GPS:

Phng php: Phn tch tng quan Point Biserial.

H0: Khng c mi quan h tuyn tnh gia GPS v gi.

H1: C mi quan h tuyn tnh no gia GPS v gi.

new_data<-data
new_data[new_data$GPS == "Yes",]['GPS']<-as.integer(1)
new_data[new_data$GPS == "No",]['GPS']<-as.integer(0)
new_data$GPS<-as.numeric(new_data$GPS)
cor.test(new_data$Price,new_data$GPS)
## 
##  Pearson's product-moment correlation
## 
## data:  new_data$Price and new_data$GPS
## t = 2.4946, df = 1359, p-value = 0.01273
## alternative hypothesis: true correlation is not equal to 0
## 95 percent confidence interval:
##  0.01442987 0.12021886
## sample estimates:
##        cor 
## 0.06751412

cor != 0=> C mi quan h tuyn tnh gia GPS v gi.

Wifi v Bluetooth:

Do mu in thoi khng c wifi v bluetooth qu t nn khng th kim nh.

Phn 4: M hnh ho d liu

Chnh sa li data ph hp vi hm tuyn tnh:

new_data<-data
#new_data$Model<-as.numeric(as.factor(new_data$Model))
#i bin Touchscreen v dng s
new_data[new_data$Touchscreen == "Yes",]$Touchscreen<-as.integer(1)
new_data[new_data$Touchscreen == "No",]$Touchscreen<-as.integer(0)
new_data$Touchscreen<-as.numeric(new_data$Touchscreen)
#i bin OS v dng s
new_data$OS = as.numeric(as.factor(new_data$OS))
#i bin Bluetooth v dng s
new_data[new_data$Bluetooth == "Yes",]['Bluetooth']<-as.integer(1)
new_data[new_data$Bluetooth == "No",]['Bluetooth']<-as.integer(0)
new_data$Bluetooth<-as.numeric(new_data$Bluetooth)
#i bin Wifi v dng s

regression_data<-train_data
regression_data$Brand<-as.numeric(as.factor(regression_data$Brand))
regression<-lm(regression_data$Price ~
     regression_data$Brand+
     regression_data$Battery+
     regression_data$Screensize+
     regression_data$Touchscreen+
     regression_data$Resolution.x+
     regression_data$Resolution.y+
     regression_data$NumOfProcessor+
     regression_data$Ram+
     regression_data$InternalStorage+
     regression_data$RearCamera+
     regression_data$FrontCamera+
     regression_data$OS+
     regression_data$Wifi+
     regression_data$Bluetooth+
     regression_data$GPS+
     regression_data$NumOfSims+
     regression_data$`3G`+
     regression_data$`4G`
   ,data = regression_data)
summary(regression)

fn_RegressionBasedOnBrand<-function(test_data,new_data){
  #Sp xp li theo Brand
  test_data<-test_data[order(test_data$Brand),]
  #result lu tr gi d on
  result<-data.frame(Name = test_data$Name,
                     Price = test_data$Price,
                     PredictedPrice=NA)
  #lp tng dng
  for (i in 1:nrow(test_data))
  {
    #Kim tra iu kin
    if (!test_data[i,]$Brand %in% new_data$Brand)
    {
      print(paste("Brand",test_data[i,]$Brand, "khng tn ti trong database!"))
      next
    }
    else if (!test_data[i,]$OS %in% new_data$OS)
    {
      print(paste("OS khng tn ti trong database!"))
      next
    }
    #To model cho Brand  hin ti
    regression_data<-new_data[new_data$Brand == test_data[i,]$Brand,]
    regression<-lm(regression_data$Price ~
     regression_data$Battery+
     regression_data$Screensize+
     regression_data$Touchscreen+
     regression_data$Resolution.x+
     regression_data$Resolution.y+
     regression_data$NumOfProcessor+
     regression_data$Ram+
     regression_data$InternalStorage+
     regression_data$RearCamera+
     regression_data$FrontCamera+
     regression_data$OS+
     regression_data$Wifi+
     regression_data$Bluetooth+
     regression_data$GPS+
     regression_data$NumOfSims+
     regression_data$`3G`+
     regression_data$`4G`
   ,data = regression_data)
    regression_data<-test_data[i,]
    #on gi  dng hin ti
    result[i,]$PredictedPrice <- predict(regression,regression_data)
  } 
  return(result)
}
suppressWarnings({
  modelForeachBrand<-fn_RegressionBasedOnBrand(test_data,train_data)
})
## [1] "OS khng tn ti trong database!"
modelForeachBrand<-modelForeachBrand%>%
  mutate(error= PredictedPrice-Price,sq.error = error^2)

k-NN:

One-hot encoding:

kNN_train_data<-train_data

#Thm ct cho tp kNN_train_data theo 
for (i in 1:nrow(brand_numOfPhone))
{
  #Ly gi unique trong ct Brand ri to ct mi theo Brand 
  new_column_name<-brand_numOfPhone[i,]$brand
  #Gn tt c gi tr ca ct  bng 0
  kNN_train_data[new_column_name]<-0
}
#Gn encoding cho tp kNN_train_data:
for (i in 1:nrow(kNN_train_data))
{
  #Ly Brand ca ct 
  column_name<-kNN_train_data[i,]$Brand
  #Gn gi tr 1 vi ct c tn ging vi column_name
  kNN_train_data[i,column_name]<-1
}
kNN_train_data<-subset(kNN_train_data,select = -c(X,Name,Brand,Model))

  #Ly gi unique trong ct Brand ri to ct mi theo Brand 
  new_column_name<-brand_numOfPhone[i,]$brand

  kNN_test_data[new_column_name]<-0
}

{
  #Ly Brand ca ct 
  column_name<-kNN_test_data[i,]$Brand
  #Gn gi tr 1 vi ct c tn ging vi column_name
  kNN_test_data[i,column_name]<-1
}

tuneGrid<-expand.grid(k=seq(1,59, by=2))

kNNModel<-train(Price~.,data = kNN_train_data, method = 'knn', 
                preProcess = c('center','scale'), 
                trControl = trainControl(method ='repeatedcv',number=10,repeats = 5),tuneGrid = tuneGrid)
